      "@id": "asbval:assertion/card/10_1038_nmeth_4197__task_001/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Salmon consists of three components: a lightweight-mapping model, an online phase that estimates initial expression levels and model parameters, and an offline phase that refines expression estimates... Salmon can quantify abundance either via a built-in, ultra-fast read-mapping procedure (quasi-mapping) [17], or using pre-computed alignments provided in SAM or BAM format.",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes Salmon's quantification of NumReads and TPM, but does not discuss salmon 2.0 (Rust rewrite), salmon 1.12.0 (C++ version), or selective-alignment mode. The paper is about salmon v0.8.0 (2017). The research question references versions and a comparison that are not present in the paper.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-nmeth-4197",
      "asbval:supported_raw": "partial",
      "asbval:target_artifact_id": "task_001",
      "asbval:target_artifact_kind": "card",
      "asbval:target_claim_field": "research_question",
      "asbval:target_claim_text": "How closely do the quantification results (NumReads and TPM) from salmon 2.0 (Rust rewrite) agree with salmon 1.12.0 (C++ version) when run in selective-alignment mode on the same dataset and index?",
      "eco:evidence_type": {
        "@id": "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ECO_0000361"
      },
      "prov:wasAttributedTo": "anthropic/claude-haiku-4-5-20251001",
