      "@type": "asbval:ScopeDriftAssertion",
      "asbval:drift_notes": [
        "The candidate task card describes a validation/regression test comparing a Rust port of Salmon to C++ Salmon 1.11.4 after a pufferfish bug fix. This is entirely outside the scope of the Patro et al. 2017 paper, which introduces Salmon v0.8.0 and its core algorithms.",
        "The paper makes no mention of Rust implementations, pufferfish, piscem-rs, or any version beyond 0.8.0.",
        "The expected outputs (mapping rates, NumReads correlation, EffectiveLength correlation) are specific to a regression test scenario that does not appear in the paper.",
        "The task card appears to describe a development/QA task from a much later version of Salmon (post-2017), not the original research paper."
      ],
