      "@id": "asbval:assertion/skill/biological-sequence-read-mapping/000",
      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Salmon consists of three components: a lightweight-mapping model, an online phase that estimates initial expression levels and model parameters, and an offline phase that refines expression estimates",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes a 'lightweight-mapping model' and mentions quasi-mapping as an alternative to traditional alignment, but does not explicitly name 'selective alignment', 'chaining', 'MEM extraction', or 'sketch-based mode'. The paper (2017, Salmon v0.8.0) predates the selective alignment terminology and features introduced in later versions. The core function\u2014mapping reads to transcripts for abundance quantification\u2014is present, but the specific technical terms (selective alignment, chaining, MEM extraction, sketch-based mode) are not found in these passages and appear to be from a later version of Salmon (v2.0+).",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-nmeth-4197",
