      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Salmon can quantify abundance either via a built-in, ultra-fast read-mapping procedure (quasi-mapping) [17], or using pre-computed alignments provided in SAM or BAM format... The offline phase applies either a standard EM algorithm or a variational Bayesian EM algorithm [20]",
      "asbval:note": "Paper describes Salmon with quasi-mapping and EM/VBEM, but does NOT mention 'selective alignment', 'MEM extraction', or the specific chain-pruning methodology. The paper is from 2017 and describes Salmon v0.8.0; salmon 2.0 with selective alignment appears to be a later development not covered in these passages.",
      "asbval:perspicacite_kb": "asb-paper-10-1038-nmeth-4197",
