      "@type": "asbval:ClaimAssessment",
      "asbval:evidence_quote": "Our novel quantification procedure, called Salmon, achieves greater accuracy than tools such as kallisto and eXpress... Salmon is open-source and freely-licensed (GPLv3). It is written in C++11 and is available at https://github.com/COMBINE-lab/Salmon.",
      "asbval:note": "Salmon is confirmed as the primary quantification tool written in C++11. Paper confirms it produces quantification output (quant.sf implied by TPM estimates and abundance outputs described throughout). However, the paper does not describe running Salmon twice for cross-version validation or producing SAM outputs for comparison.",
